WEBVTT

00:23.672 --> 00:26.372
Now, we know that you've
received upwards of £100

00:26.424 --> 00:28.875
from Mr. Mathews, the
so-called mayor of New York.

00:28.877 --> 00:32.378
And Governor Tryon. Your pulse beats
high in the Tories' game, gentlemen.

00:32.430 --> 00:35.048
Now, tell me, who else in this camp

00:35.100 --> 00:36.883
is under British pay?

00:37.769 --> 00:39.485
What are you offering?

00:40.021 --> 00:41.566
So there are others.

00:43.024 --> 00:45.441
<i>(drums continue)</i>

00:48.146 --> 00:51.281
(whispering)

00:51.316 --> 00:53.199
Ben: <i>The offer is that you hang</i>

00:53.234 --> 00:55.568
<i>for counterfeiting, not for treason.</i>

00:55.570 --> 00:58.037
I wish to be hanged for treason.

00:58.073 --> 01:01.074
To mutiny against you
traitors is an act of honor.

01:02.327 --> 01:04.410
If you hang as a forger,

01:04.412 --> 01:06.546
your family may escape reprisal.

01:06.581 --> 01:09.082
If you're marked as an
assassin, I cannot...

01:09.084 --> 01:11.501
We aren't going to hang.

01:15.507 --> 01:17.557
You're going to trade us.

01:17.592 --> 01:19.309
(scoffs)

01:19.344 --> 01:21.260
For Culper.

01:25.266 --> 01:27.433
Where did you hear that name?

01:28.269 --> 01:30.770
<i>(drums continue)</i>

01:36.077 --> 01:37.944
Where did you hear that name?!

01:39.864 --> 01:42.193
Sergeant Hickey must have heard it

01:42.218 --> 01:44.057
while standing guard outside my tent.

01:47.839 --> 01:51.457
The first man to tell me the
true name of our Agent Culper

01:51.459 --> 01:54.043
will be traded to safety on Saturday.

01:56.214 --> 01:58.715
The other man will hang tomorrow.

01:59.601 --> 02:01.718
<i>(wind whistling)</i>

02:09.360 --> 02:11.310
They don't know.

02:15.900 --> 02:19.652
The accused... Colonel William Bradford

02:19.654 --> 02:22.622
and Sergeant Thomas Hickey...

02:22.657 --> 02:25.625
having been found guilty on the charge

02:25.660 --> 02:28.294
<i>of attempting to pass</i>
<i>counterfeit bills...</i>

02:28.329 --> 02:30.380
My aim was to kill Washington,

02:30.415 --> 02:32.915
Putnam, and any other... ah!

02:34.669 --> 02:37.720
(crowd shouting)

02:39.841 --> 02:42.558
- (choking)
- Man: <i> Have you no mercy?</i>

02:43.678 --> 02:46.345
You! Are you mad?

02:46.398 --> 02:48.014
Get off me!

02:48.066 --> 02:50.149
What's wrong with you?

02:50.185 --> 02:51.317
(grunts)

02:51.352 --> 02:53.519
<i>(crowd shouting)</i>

02:53.571 --> 02:55.071
Washington: <i>Gentlemen, please.</i>

02:55.106 --> 02:56.439
- (gagging)
- Man: <i> Vengeance!</i>

02:56.491 --> 02:57.607
<i>Vengeance!</i>

02:57.659 --> 02:59.826
<i>(men grunting)</i>

